@NODE Requirements "FileMaster 3.0: Requirements"

@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

Depending on version FileMaster 3.0 needs Kickstart version 2.0 or
Kickstart 3.0 and 68020 CPU or better.
FileMaster 3.0 needs reqtools.library for screen mode and palette requesters.
Powerpacker.library is needed only if you want to take advantage
of FileMaster's automatic decrunch of @{"Show Asc/Hex/" link CMD_ShowAsc}@{"Pic" link CMD_ShowPic} and @{"Hear" link CMD_Hear}-commands.
Reqtools.library and powerpacker.library are copyright © Nico François.

@ENDNODE
@NODE Usage "How to use FileMaster 3.0"
@{i}
@{b}            @{u}FileMaster 3.0 Beta 2.3 -- Disk operating utility@{uu}

             Copyright © Toni Wilen, August 1995. Shareware.
@{ui}

	@{" Miscellaneous " link Miscellaneous}          Miscellaneous usage information
	@{" Keyboard support " link Keyboardsupport}       Usage of keyboard

	@{" Build-in Commands" link BuildinCmds}       Explanation of commands
	@{" Configuration " link Configuration}          Settings of FileMaster

@ENDNODE
@NODE Miscellaneous "FileMaster 3.0: Miscellaneous"

@{u}@{b}Miscellaneous information@{uu}@{ub}

When doubleclicking a file with the left mouse button, FileMaster first
checks @{"user commands" link CON_User} for match and executes it if match is found.
If no user commands match then FileMaster executes the appropriate
@{"build-in command" link BuildinCmds} according to file type. For example when you doubleclick
a textfile, FileMaster will automatically use @{"ShowAsc" link CMD_ShowAsc} to view it.

You can use key shortcuts to select gadgets without mouse. Shortcut
key is marked with underscore except on menu bar and buttons on
bottom-right of screen.

Right mouse button can be used to abort most of the build-in commands.

You can rename and format volumes by clicking operate-gadget when the
approriate device is selected from device list.
Note: for safety FileMaster only formats devices smaller than 4MB

Right mousebutton click over free/used string above directory window
rereads directory and over vertical proportional gadget goes to
parent directory.

'<' and '>' below the directory windows goes to next and previous directory
buffer. Number between arrows shows the number of the buffer (0-9) and by
clicking it you can select directory buffer from a list.
'M' opens @{"pattern match window" link PatternMatch}

When for example copying you can click '<' and '>' gadgets to move
to next/previous directory buffer and do something with them while
FileMaster continues copying. (@{"Multitasking" link CON_GENERAL} must be active)

@{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

Usage:	@{b}FileMaster@{ub} [-s]
The '-s' option puts FileMaster to sleep like @{"Sleep" link CMD_Sleep}-gadget.

@ENDNODE
@NODE PatternMatch "FileMaster 3.0: Pattern match"

Each directory window can have different sort and pattern match
parameters. Default is shown in parenthesis.

@{b}Sort by@{ub}		sort directories by name, size or date (name)
		sorting can be ascending or descending (ascending)
@{b}Mix files with directories@{ub} (don't mix)
@{b}Display drawers last@{ub} (display drawers first)
@{b}Name@{ub}		name pattern (*)
		off/case sensitive/insensitive (case insensitive)
@{b}Size@{ub}		file size (0)
		off/equal/nonenqual/smaller than/larger than (off)
@{b}Flags@{ub}		pattern for protection flags ()
@{b}Date@{ub}		date (system's time when FileMaster was started)
		off/older than/newer than (off)
@{b}Files@{ub}		match,match always,don't match (match)
@{b}Dirs@{ub}		match,match always,don't match (match)

Files and directories not matched are not displayed.

'@{b}xx@{ub}/@{b}yy@{ub}/@{b}zz@{ub} files @{b}xx@{ub}/@{b}yy@{ub}/@{b}zz@{ub} directories @{b}xx@{ub}/@{b}yy@{ub}/@{b}zz@{ub} bytes' string means
@{b}xx@{ub}=files or directories selected
@{b}yy@{ub}=files or directories matched (displayed on screen and can be selected)
@{b}zz@{ub}=total files or directories (matched+not matched)

@ENDNODE
@NODE Keyboardsupport "FileMaster 3.0: Keyboard support"

@{b}@{u}Keyboard support@{ub}

FileMaster has full keyboard support.@{uu}

cursor keys move selector-cursor.
shift+cursor keys move cursor faster and ctrl+cursor keys move
to the beginning or to the end of the list.
return is same as left mousebutton and shift-return right.
tab selects next directory window and shift-tab selects previous.
Gadgets which have key shortcuts can be cancelled by pressing control-key
while keeping the shortcut key pressed.

@ENDNODE
